t: "When one is touched with hardship, they cry out to their Lord, turning to Him ňĻaloneňļ. But as soon as He showers them with blessings from Him, they ňĻtotallyňļ forget the One they had cried to earlier, and set up equals to God to mislead ňĻothersňļ from His Way. Say, ňĻO Prophet,ňļ ‚ÄúEnjoy your disbelief for a little while! You will certainly be one of the inmates of the Fire.‚ÄĚ"